name: Victoria Vivians
bio: She provides the Fever with size, strength and maturity in the backcourt and has been voted the country’s top shooting guard in 2018

name: Erica Wheeler
bio: Having completed four WNBA seasons, Erica Wheeler established herself as a starter and regular contributor with the Fever

name: Kelsey Mitchell
bio: A left-handed, dynamic scorer with a high-powered scorer’s mentality and is the most heralded player ever to come out of Ohio State

name: Tiffany Mitchell
bio: Mitchell had immediate impact with the Fever, including a game-high 18 points in her rookie debut against Dallas and she has set a franchise record with 42 consecutive made free throws

name: Teaira McCowan
bio: She guided the Bulldogs to four consecutive NCAA Tournament berths, including back-to-back appearances in the national championship game in 2017 and 2018

name: Stephanie Mavunga
bio: A three-time all-league performer in the Big Ten and ACC, she was the third Indiana Miss Basketball to enter Fever training camp

name: Candice Dupree
bio: She left Phoenix with her 34 double-digit rebounding games, the most in franchise history, including three of the top four single-game rebounding efforts in club history

name: Kennedy Burke
bio: She helped guide the Bruins to four straight NCAA Tournament appearances, reaching the Elite Eight in 2017-18

name: Natalie Achonwa
bio: She helped Canada to gold medals at the FIBA Americas Championship and she made a second Olympics appearance with Canada during the 2016 Olympics in Rio de Janeiro, Brazil
